articles.description: Wichita State coach Gregg Marshall said this has been the toughest February of his coaching career.
articles.headline: No. 19 Wichita State out for revenge vs. Temple

articles.description: Duncan Robinson scored 18 points and No. 22 Michigan beat Iowa 74-59 on Wednesday night.
articles.headline: Robinson scores 18 as Wolverines beat Hawkeyes 74-59

images.caption: Zavier Simpson's pass is intended for Charlies Matthews but instead it hits him the head and Iowa intercepts the ball before speeding to the other side of the court.
images.name: Ball hits Matthews and results in Michigan turnover

articles.description: If revenge is a dish best served cold, Arizona State should be well positioned for its second meeting with Arizona.
articles.headline: No. 25 ASU seeks revenge against rival Arizona

articles.description: Charles Matthews cuts behind two Iowa defenders to receive the lob pass from Jordan Bohannon and then throws down a two-handed dunk late in the second half.
articles.headline: Matthews gets inside for jam

articles.description: A.J. Davis had a career-high 26 points and nine rebounds, B.J. Taylor added 21 points with six assists and Central Florida beat South Florida 72-57 on Wednesday night in the War On I-4.
articles.headline: UCF beats South Florida 72-57 in the War On I-4

articles.description: Purdue will look to spoil former Wisconsin star Frank Kaminsky's homecoming on Thursday when the No. 6 Boilermakers visit the Badgers in Madison, Wis.
articles.headline: No. 6 Purdue tries to end two-game skid
